-- India Extends Commodity Regulator Khatua's Tenure, Economic Times Says
-- Madelene Pearson
-- 2010-08-01T03:18:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-01/india-extends-commodity-regulator-khatua-s-tenure-economic-times-says.html

          
          
             B.C. Khatua was granted a one year
extension to continue as chairman of the Forward Markets
Commission, India’s commodity markets regulator, the Economic
Times newspaper reported, citing Khatua.  
 Khatua’s three-year term was due to end on July 30, the
newspaper said. It will be extended until July, 2011, the report
said.   
